%20behave.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Wall%20street%20broker%20pointing%20upwards%20in%20front%20of%20an%20upward%20stock%20arrow%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66c76dff1aa2ac29ee3364b9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ESpencer%20Platt%2FGetty%2C%20Tyler%20Le%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20stock%20market%20has%20whipsawed%20so%20far%20in%202025%2C%20starting%20with%20sharp%20gains%20and%20tanking%20lately.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EA%20gauge%20of%20expected%20market%20volatility%20is%20the%20highest%20it's%20been%20in%20months.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EA%20managing%20director%20at%20CME%20Group%20lays%20out%20four%20ways%20increased%20volatility%20has%20changed%20trading%20habits.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20been%20a%20rollercoaster%20ride%20for%20stocks%20so%20far%20in%202025.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20springing%20out%20to%20a%204%25%20gain%20in%20the%20first%20three%20weeks%20of%20the%20year%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Findex%2Fs%26amp%3Bp_500%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ES%26amp%3BP%20500%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20struggled.%20Following%20a%202%25%20drop%20on%20Thursday%2C%20the%20benchmark%20index%20is%20now%20down%207%25%20since%20reaching%20all-time%20highs%20in%20mid-February.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStirring%20up%20the%20moves%20has%20been%20a%20mixture%20of%20fears%20around%20sticky%20inflation%2C%20tariff%20threats%2C%20AI%20competition%2C%20and%20geopolitical%20risks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Findex%2Fvix%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECboe%20Volatility%20Index%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20or%20VIX%2C%20commonly%20referred%20to%20as%20the%20stock%20market's%20fear%20gauge%2C%20which%20looks%20at%20expected%20price%20swings%2030%20days%20in%20the%20future%20%E2%80%94%20sits%20at%20its%20highest%20level%20since%20December.%20The%20consistent%20theme%20is%20that%20stocks%20are%20especially%20volatile%20right%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPaul%20Woolman%2C%20a%20managing%20director%20at%20CME%20Group%2C%20says%20increased%20market%20gyrations%20over%20the%20past%20two%20years%20have%20driven%20explosive%20appetite%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fstock-options%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eoptions%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Ffutures-investing%23%3A~%3Atext%3DFutures%2520contracts%2520allow%2520traders%2520to%2Cof%2520diversification%2520to%2520a%2520portfolio.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efutures%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20recent%20days%2C%20when%20the%20market%20is%20whipsawing%20around%2C%20we%20see%20elevated%20volumes%20because%20people%20are%20forced%20to%20risk%20manage%20and%20react%20to%20that%20news%20flow%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20noting%20that%20traders%20are%20increasingly%20using%20derivative%20strategies%20to%20make%20those%20moves.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDetailed%20below%20are%20four%20ways%20investors%20have%20adapted%20their%20approaches%20in%20response%20to%20an%20increasingly%20volatile%20market%20environment%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22632e7c2b-8afe-45de-bee5-9a0da96d54cf%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E(1)%20A%20move%20toward%20shorter-duration%20options%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20institutional%20investors%2C%20that's%20meant%20a%20shift%20from%20quarterly%20contracts%20to%20weekly%2C%20where%20volumes%20have%20spiked%2C%20Woolman%20noted.%20Meanwhile%2C%20the%20retail-favorite%20has%20been%20to%20go%20even%20shorter%2C%20by%20betting%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fwhat-are-zero-day-expiration-options-stock-market-risks-0dte-2023-9%23%3A~%3Atext%3DZero%252Ddays%252Dto%252Dexpiration%2Cit%2520is%2520set%2520to%2520expire.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ezero%20days%20to%20expiration%20options%3C%2Fa%3E%20(0DTE)%2C%20which%20are%20risky%20contracts%20that%20expire%20the%20same%20day%20they're%20issued.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWoolman%20said%20one%20reason%20for%20the%20shift%20is%20that%20traders%20are%20likely%20seeking%20a%20lower%20premium%20than%20they%20might%20find%20with%20a%20longer-duration%20contract%2C%20and%20instead%20continually%20rolling%20over%20into%20cheaper%2C%20shorter%20ones.%20Second%2C%20such%20an%20approach%20allows%20them%20to%20maintain%20tighter%20positions%20and%20more%20control%20in%20an%20uncertain%20environment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20lot%20of%20institutional%20clients%20and%20potentially%20retail%20clients%20want%20to%20really%20be%20very%20precise%20with%20the%20time%20that%20they're%20taking%20an%20option%20position%20over%2C%26quot%3B%20Woolman%20said.%20%26quot%3BSometimes%20they're%20targeting%20a%20specific%20event%20risk%2C%20so%20that%20might%20be%20economic%20numbers%20or%20earnings%20or%20some%20other%20event%2C%20like%20election%20events%20and%20things%20like%20that.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a09510c6-2124-45c8-bd91-22cb22b03476%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E2.%20A%20move%20toward%20more%20sophisticated%20options%20packages%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3ETraditionally%2C%20the%20most%20basic%20strategies%20have%20been%20buying%20and%20selling%20call%20or%20put%20options%20on%20major%20indexes%2C%20something%20that%20amounts%20to%20a%20straight%20directional.%20However%2C%20options%20packages%20that%20spread%20out%20exposure%20or%20double%20down%20on%20conviction%20are%20becoming%20increasingly%20popular.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20example%20of%20those%20packages%20involves%20vertical%20spreads%2C%20which%20are%20options%20contracts%20on%20an%20underlying%20asset%20that%20are%20either%20both%20a%20call%20or%20put%20but%20have%20different%20strike%20prices%20on%20the%20same%20expiry.%20It's%20a%20trade%20that%20reflects%20a%20trader's%20strong%20stance%20that%20a%20price%20will%20move%20in%20an%20expected%20direction.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStraddles%20are%20also%20gaining%20popularity%20for%20less%20directional%20conviction%20and%20more%20neutral%20positions%20that%20profit%20from%20volatility.%20In%20this%20position%2C%20a%20trader%20buys%20a%20call%20and%20put%20with%20the%20same%20strike%20price%20and%20expiration%20date%20on%20an%20underlying%20asset%20to%20leverage%20volatility%20in%20either%20direction.%20Another%20popular%20neutral%20position%20has%20been%20the%20strangle%2C%20when%20a%20trader%20buys%20or%20sells%20a%20call%20and%20put%20at%20different%20strike%20prices%20on%20the%20same%20expiry.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c25703f4-bb79-48ca-bd6d-3e8a9a78bfec%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E(3)%20Increased%20retail%20appetite%20for%20micro%20E-mini%20options%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20and%20fractional%20options%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20options%20and%20futures%20are%20about%20one-10th%20the%20size%20of%20the%20parent%20mini-contracts%20and%20have%20been%20hugely%20successful%20at%20drawing%20individual%20traders%2C%20Woolman%20noted.%20Since%20they're%20more%20accessible%20and%20bite-sized%2C%20that's%20enabled%20their%20inclusion%20on%20trading%20apps%20like%20Robinhood%2C%20something%20he%20says%20has%20generated%20growth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e184e00d-efc3-4d4b-9d62-f9af326e0e93%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E(4)%20Increased%20interest%20in%20afterhours%20contracts%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EWoolman%20says%20activity%20has%20picked%20up%20in%20the%20options%20and%20futures%20markets%20outside%20of%20regular%20daily%20trading.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20that%20news%20hits%2C%20clients%20want%20to%20react%20and%20be%20able%20to%20trade%20on%20that.%20And%20we've%20definitely%20seen%20an%20increased%20trend%20of%20people%20wanting%20to%20trade%20and%20manage%20their%20risk%20in%20a%20real-time%20manner%2C%26quot%3B%20Woolman%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20table%20below%20shows%20the%20dates%20that%20saw%20the%20highest%20all-time%20volumes%20for%20equity-index-option%20products%20tracking%20the%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%2C%20tech-heavy%20Nasdaq%20100%2C%20the%20Dow%2C%20and%20the%20small-cap-heavy%20Russell%202000%20in%20after-hours%20trading%20between%206%20p.m.%20and%209%20a.m.%20ET.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20fact%20that%20five%20of%20the%20top%2010%20days%20have%20come%20in%20the%20last%20year%20shows%20how%20demand%20for%20these%20products%20has%20accelerated%20alongside%20market%20volatility.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22807%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Table%20for%20after%20hours%20trading%20volumes.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67caf08069253ccddf9891d2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22275%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAfter-hours%20trading%20volumes.%3Cp%3ECME%20data%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstock-market-trading-hedging-strategy-changes-increased-volatility-cme-group-2025-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1741516201000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67ca0927585f1dff88b168b2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstock-market-trading-hedging-strategy-changes-increased-volatility-cme-group-2025-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20stock%20market's%20increased%20volatility%20has%20investors%20rethinking%20how%20they%20make%20bets%20and%20protect%20their%20money.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22lmaidan%40businessinsider.com%20(Laila%20Maidan)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstock-market-trading-hedging-strategy-changes-increased-volatility-cme-group-2025-3%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22CD%2C%20Checking%2C%20and%20Savings%20Rates%20Today%3A%20Grow%20Your%20