ing-notifications-melting-icon-gen-z-marketing-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDuolingo%3C%2Fa%3E%20so%20he%20can%20practice%20his%20English.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESaumure%20is%20one%20of%20several%20travel%20content%20creators%20who%20have%20gone%20to%20Afghanistan%20since%20the%20United%20States%20ended%20its%20longest%20war%20and%20evacuated%20the%20country.%20They're%20mostly%20men%20%E2%80%94%20sometimes%20traveling%20in%20groups%20on%20boys'%20trips.%20For%20a%20certain%20kind%20of%20manosphere%20influencer%20eager%20for%20an%20edge%20in%20the%20attention%20economy%2C%20Jalalabad%20is%20the%20new%20Nashville.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20summer%20of%202021%2C%20a%2021-year-old%20British%20student%20named%20Miles%20Routledge%20visited%20Afghanistan%20after%20seeing%20it%20on%20a%20list%20of%20the%20world's%20most%20dangerous%20places.%20(He%20had%20previously%20visited%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-blames-russia-for-attack-on-chernobyls-radiation-shield-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChernobyl%3C%2Fa%3E.)%20Notably%2C%20Routledge%20was%20stranded%20during%20the%20fall%20of%20Kabul%20that%20August%20and%20had%20to%20be%20evacuated%20by%20the%20British%20army.%20When%20he%20returned%20in%202023%2C%20he%20was%20imprisoned%20by%20the%20Taliban%20for%20several%20months.%20He%20claims%20he%20was%20treated%20well%2C%20watching%20movies%20and%20playing%20Xbox%20with%20members.%20%26quot%3BIt%20was%20a%20good%20setup%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says%20in%20a%20video.%20%26quot%3BBasically%2C%20I%20was%20chilling.%26quot%3B%20Routledge%20didn't%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20predominating%20sentiment%20in%20these%20videos%20is%20that%20Afghanistan%20is%20misunderstood%2C%20portrayed%20by%20the%20West%20as%20hostile%20and%20dangerous%20while%20it's%20actually%20warm%20and%20welcoming.%20%26quot%3BF*%40K%20the%20Media%3A%20I%20Went%20to%20AFGHANISTAN!%26quot%3B%20one%20traveler%20titled%20his%20video%3B%20another%20clip%20is%20called%20%26quot%3BAfghanistan%20is%20NOT%20What%20You%20Think!%26quot%3B%20Some%20show%20beautiful%20mountains%20and%20mosques%20and%20detail%20warm%20interactions%20with%20locals.%20There's%20more%20shocking%20fare%2C%20such%20as%20%26quot%3BI%20Went%20Shooting%20with%20the%20Taliban%2C%26quot%3B%20or%20videos%20about%20exploring%20decades-old%20abandoned%20Russian%20tanks.%20A%20YouTuber%20called%20Arab%20who%20runs%20a%20channel%20with%201.8%20million%20subscribers%20calls%20himself%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftravel-with-kids-memories-for-parents-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eadventure%20traveler%3C%2Fa%3E%20but%20says%20in%20a%20disclaimer%20that%20he's%20going%20for%20journalistic%20purposes.%20His%20goofy%2C%20spirited%20hourlong%20videos%20include%20%26quot%3BThe%20Young%20Taliban%20Train%20Me%20For%20War%2C%26quot%3B%20where%20he%20plays%20with%20children%20dressed%20in%20camo%20and%20holding%20toy%20guns%2C%20and%20%26quot%3BI%20Spent%207%20Days%20Living%20with%20the%20Taliban.%26quot%3B%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EHe%20didn't%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20an%20interview.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20creators%20are%20also%20wading%20into%20a%20country%20that%20many%20Western%20governments%20warn%20against%20traveling%20to%2C%20one%20that%20has%20been%20ravaged%20by%20war%20and%20is%20now%20under%20an%20oppressive%20unelected%20government.%20Freedom%20of%20expression%20and%20religious%20practices%20that%20don't%20conform%20to%20sharia%2C%20or%20Islamic%20law%2C%20are%20restricted%3B%20girls%20must%20leave%20school%20at%2012%3B%20and%20Taliban%20members%20have%20attacked%20queer%20people.%20In%202024%2C%20three%20Spanish%20tourists%20and%20three%20Afghans%20were%20killed%20in%20a%20shooting%20in%20a%20bazaar%20%E2%80%94%20the%20Islamic%20State%20claimed%20responsibility%20for%20the%20attack.%20In%20January%2C%20two%20Americans%20were%20freed%20in%20a%20prisoner%20swap%20for%20a%20Taliban%20member.%20In%20late%20February%2C%20the%20Taliban%20arrested%20a%20British%20couple%20in%20their%2070s%2C%20though%20the%20Taliban%20described%20their%20detention%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bmisunderstanding.%26quot%3B%20The%20US%20Department%20of%20State%20advises%20citizens%20not%20to%20travel%20to%20Afghanistan%2C%20citing%20%26quot%3Bcivil%20unrest%2C%20crime%2C%20terrorism%2C%20risk%20of%20wrongful%20detention%2C%20kidnapping%2C%20and%20limited%20health%20facilities.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20of%20these%20travelers%20aren't%20strangers%20to%20some%20sense%20of%20danger.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EAfghanistan%20offers%20the%20kind%20of%20exclusive%20content%20certain%20to%20lure%20eyes%2C%20especially%20if%20the%20vloggers%20can%20interact%20and%20bro%20out%20with%20a%20notorious%20extremist%20group.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESaumure%20tells%20me%20that%20after%20traveling%20to%20several%20%26quot%3Bdangerous%26quot%3B%20countries%2C%20including%20Iraq%20and%20Pakistan%2C%20%26quot%3Byou%20kind%20of%20start%20to%20disengage%20from%20all%20the%20level-four%20warnings%20that%20your%20government%20might%20say%20about%20traveling%20to%20these%20places%20and%20just%20not%20trust%20your%20own%20government%20and%20go%20based%20on%20what%20other%20travelers%20are%20saying.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20he%20still%20witnessed%20the%20country's%20deep-rooted%20issues.%20%26quot%3BEven%20if%20the%20west%20is%20maybe%20selling%20a%20very%20sensational%20narrative%2C%20I%20still%20saw%20the%20oppression%20firsthand%20as%20far%20as%20women%20not%20being%20allowed%20in%20certain%20parks%20and%20modesty%20laws%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20delicate%20subject.%20I%20just%20wanted%20to%20be%20like%2C%20'this%20is%20how%20it%20is%20here%2C'%20instead%20of%20driving%20into%20my%20beliefs.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20growing%20interest%20to%20experience%20places%20firsthand%20%E2%80%94%20or%20at%20least%20watch%20some%20other%20amateur%20do%20it%20%E2%80%94%20underscores%20a%20growing%20distrust%20of%20institutions%20and%20authority.%20In%20a%202024%20survey%20by%20the%20Pew%20Research%20Center%2C%20about%20one%20in%20five%20Americans%20said%20they%20got%20their%20news%20from%20influencers%20on%20social%20media.%20That%20figure%20jumped%20to%2037%25%20for%20respondents%20under%2030.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20dangerous%20as%20Western%20governments%20say%20Afghanistan%20is%2C%20the%20country%20wants%20tourists%2C%20particularly%20those%20who%20show%20a%20different%20side%20of%20the%20country%20than%20news%20reports%20show%2C%20and%20it%20advertises%20tourism%20on%20its%20websites.%20Afghanistan's%20Ministry%20of%20Information%20and%20Culture%20didn't%20respond%20to%20my%20request%20for%20comment.%20Taliban%20officials%20told%20The%20New%20York%20Times%20last%20year%20that%20some%2014%2C500%20foreigners%20had%20visited%20Afghanistan%20since%202021%2C%20most%20of%20them%20men.%20Several%20tourism%20companies%20and%20travel%20agencies%20have%20popped%20up%20to%20help%20eager%20travelers%20navigate%20the%20country.%20The%20rebrand%20of%20Afghanistan%20has%20been%20underway%20for%20years%20%E2%80%94%20shortly%20after%20the%20fall%20of%20Kabul%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-viral-memes-did-the-talibans-bidding-by-helping-them-rebrand-2021-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Evideos%20of%20Taliban%20fighters%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20became%20memeified%2C%20showing%20them%20doing%20silly%20activities%20like%20riding%20a%20carousel.%20Some%20researchers%20worried%20at%20the%20time%20that%20the%20content%20could%20help%20soften%20the%20group's%20image.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECarrie%20Patsalis%2C%20a%2048-year-old%20British%20travel%20vlogger%2C%20toured%20Afghanistan%20with%20a%20guide%20for%2010%20days%20in%20May.%20%26quot%3BThe%20world%20has%20a%20really%20funny%20narrative%20and%20a%20really%20funny%20idea%20about%20which%20countries%20you%20should%20shun%20based%20on%20unelected%20regimes%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20She%20argues%20that%20staying%20away%20hurts%20the%20country's%20economy%20%E2%80%94%20UN%20officials%20have%20estimated%20that%20about%2085%25%20of%20Afghans%20live%20on%20less%20than%20%241%20a%20day%20%E2%80%94%20and%20the%20Afghan%20people%20who%20may%20not%20support%20the%20Taliban%20rule.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20thinks%20travel%20vloggers%20should%20show%20both%20the%20country's%20beauty%20and%20its%20oppression.%20Patsalis%20tells%20me%20she%20made%20a%20point%20to%20seek%20out%20women%20on%20her%20trip.%20She%20tells%20me%20that%20while%20the%20women%20could%20not%20be%20seen%20on%20camera%2C%20she%20wanted%20to%20let%20them%20know%20that%20%26quot%3BI%20see%20you%2C%20I%20know%20you're%20here%2C%20and%20it%20matters%20to%20me%20how%20you%20live.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUltimately%2C%20going%20to%20Afghanistan%20is%20good%20business%20for%20travel%20content%20creators%20competing%20for%20eyes%20in%20an%20online%20world%20full%20of%20travel%20recommendations.%20Harry%20Jaggard%2C%20a%20British%2027-year-old%20who%20has%20been%20making%20videos%20for%20three%20years%2C%20says%20his%20series%20in%20Afghanistan%20in%202023%20was%20his%20most%20successful.%20He%20tells%20me%20he's%20traveling%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnorth-korea-behind-bybit-crypto-hack-fbi-billion-dollar-heist-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENorth%20Korea%3C%2Fa%3E%20next%20month.%20%26quot%3BTo%20be%20the%20best%2C%20you%20sometimes%20have%20to%20push%20the%20boundaries%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20%26quot%3BEveryone%20wants%20to%20see%20it%2C%20and%20not%20many%20people%20go%20there.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20series%2C%20Jaggard%20travels%20with%20a%20guide%20and%20meets%20men%20who%20he%20says%20are%20members%20of%20the%20Taliban%20in%20the%20street.%20(He%20says%20he%20learned%20to%20tell%20by%20looking%20at%20their%20clothing%20and%20asking%20his%20guide.)%20He%20says%20that%20while%20he%20was%20apprehensive%2C%20he%20found%20the%20Taliban%20members%20to%20be%20shockingly%20friendly.%20%26quot%3BThey're%20outwardly%20very%20kind%20%E2%80%94%20that's%20how%20they%20gain%20your%20trust%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20tells%20me.%20But%20he%20didn't%20want%20to%20highlight%20too%20much%20of%20the%20Taliban%20in%20his%20videos%3B%20he%20says%20he%20focused%20on%20meeting%20citizens%2C%20whom%20he%20described%20as%20among%20the%20most%20hospitable%20people%20he's%20encountered%20in%20the%20dozens%20of%20countries%20he%20has%20traveled%20to.%20He%20says%20it's%20a%20reminder%20that%20%26quot%3Ba%20government%20and%20its%20people%20are%20two%20different%20things.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20videos%20also%20fill%20a%20gap%20in%20traditional%20travel%20journalism.%20%26quot%3BFrommer's%20would%20never%20cover%20travel%20to%20a%20place%20that%20is%20as%20dangerous%20as%20this%20one%20is%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Pauline%20Frommer%2C%20the%20publisher%20of%20Frommer's%20Guidebooks%2C%20the%20popular%20guidebook%20series%20that%20has%20been%20around%20since%20the%201950s.%20While%20encouraging%20other%20people%20to%20travel%20to%20places%20like%20Afghanistan%20despite%20government%20warnings%20is%20dangerous%2C%20there%20are%20insights%20to%20be%20gleaned%20from%20watching%20travel%20vloggers%20have%20first-hand%20experiences%20there%2C%20and%20many%20people%20can%20learn%20from%20watching%20them.%20%26quot%3BI%20see%20nothing%20wrong%20with%20videos%20about%20less%20visited%20parts%20of%20the%20world%2C%26quot%3B%20Frommer%20tells%20me.%20%26quot%3BI%20find%20value%20in%20looking%20at%20what%20daily%20life%20is%20like.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20now%2C%20Afghanistan%20isn't%20overrun%20with%20selfie%20sticks%20at%20landmarks%20and%20TikTokers%20crowding%20local%20restaurants.%20But%20the%20need%20to%20keep%20content%20interesting%20is%20pushing%20these%20creators%20to%20more%20controversial%20and%20dangerous%20places%2C%20as%20curious%20viewers%20want%20to%2